  "conclusion": "On the FIRST genuinely-powered, leakage-controlled, real-stakes substrate (DockQ base rate 50% at >=0.49; ipTM->DockQ 0.865), the project's headline is confirmed across 3 models incl. non-Anthropic GPT-4.1: (1) raw calibrated confidence genuinely helps (raw - no_signal = +0.07..+0.32, and raw is the best arm) - unlike the saturated monomer set where it was trivial; (2) the calibrated reliability INTERFACE does not beat raw and is consistently -0.07 worse (it induces over-verification; Opus collapses to verify-all under any risk card); (3) cue-following persists (inverted control degrades routing). Raw confidence is the robust lever; presentation-layer reliability interfaces are not a free win - motivating enforcement-based routing."
